35#ifndef lib_funcattrs_h
36#define lib_funcattrs_h
37
38/*
39 * Attributes to apply to functions and their arguments, using various
40 * compiler-specific extensions.
41 */
42
43/*
44 * This was introduced by Clang:
45 *
46 * http://clang.llvm.org/docs/LanguageExtensions.html#has-attribute
47 *
48 * in some version (which version?); it has been picked up by GCC 5.0.
49 */
50#ifndef __has_attribute
51 /*
52 * It's a macro, so you can check whether it's defined to check
53 * whether it's supported.
54 *
55 * If it's not, define it to always return 0, so that we move on to
56 * the fallback checks.
57 */
58 #define __has_attribute(x) 0
59#endif
60
61/*
62 * NORETURN, before a function declaration, means "this function
63 * never returns". (It must go before the function declaration, e.g.
64 * "extern NORETURN func(...)" rather than after the function
65 * declaration, as the MSVC version has to go before the declaration.)
66 */
67#if __has_attribute(noreturn) \
68 || (defined(__GNUC__) && ((__GNUC__ * 100 + __GNUC_MINOR__) >= 205)) \
69 || (defined(__SUNPRO_C) && (__SUNPRO_C >= 0x590)) \
70 || (defined(__xlC__) && __xlC__ >= 0x0A01) \
71 || (defined(__HP_aCC) && __HP_aCC >= 61000)
72 /*
73 * Compiler with support for __attribute((noreturn)), or GCC 2.5 and
74 * later, or Solaris Studio 12 (Sun C 5.9) and later, or IBM XL C 10.1
75 * and later (do any earlier versions of XL C support this?), or
76 * HP aCC A.06.10 and later.
77 */
78 #define NORETURN __attribute((noreturn))
79#elif defined(_MSC_VER)
80 /*
81 * MSVC.
82 */
83 #define NORETURN __declspec(noreturn)
84#else
85 #define NORETURN
86#endif
87
88/*
89 * PRINTFLIKE(x,y), after a function declaration, means "this function
90 * does printf-style formatting, with the xth argument being the format
91 * string and the yth argument being the first argument for the format
92 * string".
93 */
94#if __has_attribute(__format__) \
95 || (defined(__GNUC__) && ((__GNUC__ * 100 + __GNUC_MINOR__) >= 203)) \
96 || (defined(__xlC__) && __xlC__ >= 0x0A01) \
97 || (defined(__HP_aCC) && __HP_aCC >= 61000)
98 /*
99 * Compiler with support for it, or GCC 2.3 and later, or IBM XL C 10.1
100 * and later (do any earlier versions of XL C support this?),
101 * or HP aCC A.06.10 and later.
102 */
103 #define PRINTFLIKE(x,y) __attribute__((__format__(__printf__,x,y)))
104#else
105 #define PRINTFLIKE(x,y)
106#endif
107
108/*
109 * For flagging arguments as format strings in MSVC.
110 */
111#if _MSC_VER >= 1400
112 #include <sal.h>
113 #if _MSC_VER > 1400
114 #define FORMAT_STRING(p) _Printf_format_string_ p
115 #else
116 #define FORMAT_STRING(p) __format_string p
117 #endif
118#else
119 #define FORMAT_STRING(p) p
120#endif
121
122#endif /* lib_funcattrs_h */
